{% block body %}
    <div class="sketch-api">
        <div class="sk-sidebar sk-sidebar-right">
            <div class="sk-guide sk-pane selected">
                <div class="sk-header" style="font-size:0.8em; letter-spacing: 1px">The Basics: Click below for detail
                </div>
                <div class="sk-divider">
                    <label><input type="checkbox"></label> Invention Title
                    <div>Your title should be descriptive, providing a high level understanding of the invention.  Typically, it includes the terms apparatus, system, and/or method/process..</div>
                </div>
                <div class="sk-divider">
                    <label><input type="checkbox"></label> Inventor(s) Information
                    <div>An inventor is anyone who contributes to an element of the claims of the invention. Include: Names, Mailing Addresses, Country of Residence</div>
                </div>
                <div class="sk-divider">
                    <label><input type="checkbox"></label> Background
                    <div>Background information sets the stage for what your invention is and the problem it solves.  The background can include the answers to questions such as: What is the problem you are attempting to solve? How did you find out about the problem? What does the prior art do to address the problem? What does the prior art fail to do?</div>
                </div>
                <div class="sk-divider">
                    <label><input type="checkbox"></label> Summary
                    <div>This is a high level overview of your invention and should list the major components of your apparatus or system, or the primary steps in your method/process.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="sk-divider">
                    <label><input type="checkbox"></label> Detailed Description
                    <div>Each component (or step) of the invention should be described in detail as well as any alternative embodiments, for example, if the invention includes a valve, then alternatives could be a ball valve, a check valve, a reed valve, etc.  The detailed description should refer to the figures such that the reader can better understand the structure or process being discussed.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="sk-divider">
                    <label><input type="checkbox"></label> Figures
                    <div>The figures should show each component of the invention. Typically, for most mechanical type inventions, the complete apparatus is shown, then subsequent figures show the internal portions via a cutaway or individual components.  Electrical schematics are used as are block diagrams for methods/processes.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="sk-divider">
                    <label><input type="checkbox"></label> Process/Method (E.g. Software)
                    <div>While software can be described as a system (compilation of software modules operated by a processor), it is also easily described as a method/process.  Focus on describing what was not possible in the prior art and how the process solves the problem.  Each step should be described fully, e.g., what are the inputs, what happens, what is the output, what are the alternatives, etc.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="sk-divider">
                    <label><input type="checkbox"></label> Primary Advantages/Benefits
                    <div>The advantages and benefits of your invention will help understand the breadth of your invention.  Benefits can include efficiency, cost, weight, or specific benefit based on the problem being addressed.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="sk-divider">
                    <label><input type="checkbox"></label> Potential Claims
                    <div>Claims defined the scope of your invention.  Typically, there is an introduction: "An apparatus for sitting comprising..." followed by a number of elements/components whose relationship to one another is described:"a leg member; a seat member coupled to the leg member..."</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="sk-search sk-pane">
                <div class="sk-header">search</div>
                <a href="http://www.google.com/patents/related" target="_blank" data-title="Link to Google patent search.">Search for prior art</a>
                <a href="#" target="_blank" data-title="Estimation of lifecycle cost of patent">Patent Cost Calculator (not yet active)</a>
                <a href="http://www.uspto.gov/patent/laws-regulations-policies-procedures-guidance-and-training" target="_blank" data-title="Links to patent laws and rules">Patent laws and rules</a>
                <a href="http://www.uspto.gov/learning-and-resources/inventors-entrepreneurs-resources" target="_blank" data-title="USPTO inventor resources.">USPTO inventor assistance</a>
                <a href="http://www.uspto.gov/patent/forms/forms-patent-applications-filed-or-after-september-16-2012" target="_blank" data-title="Link to USPTO Forms Page">Forms for Patent Filing</a>
            </div>
            <div class="sk-help sk-pane">
                <div class="sk-header">help</div>
                <div style="margin: 10px;">
                    <p>Subject</p>
                    <input name="subject" type="text" />
                    <p>Email</p>
                    <input name="email" type="text" placeholder="you@domain.com" />
                    <p>Message</p>
                    <textarea name="content"></textarea>
                    <input type="submit" class="button" value="Send" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sk-sidebar sk-sidebar-left">
            <span class="tabs"></span>

            <!--- CONFIGURE -->
            <div id="sk-configure" class="sk-pane"></div>

            <!--- CONFIGURE: FILL -->
            <div id="sk-configure-fill" class="sk-pane">
                <div class="sk-header"><span class="icon-left to-configure"></span>fill</div>
                <div class="sk-pane-content"></div>
            </div>

            <!--- CONFIGURE: STROKE -->
            <div id="sk-configure-stroke" class="sk-pane">
                <div class="sk-header"><span class="icon-left to-configure"></span>stroke</div>
                <div class="sk-pane-content"></div>
            </div>

            <!--- LAYERS -->
            <div id="sk-layers" class="sk-pane">
                <div class="sk-header">layers</div>		
                <ul class="sk-pane-content sk-tree"></ul>
            </div>

            <!--- DOCUMENT: HISTORY -->
            <div id="sk-history" class="sk-pane">
                <div class="sk-header">History</div>
                <ul class="sk-pane-content sk-tree"></ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sk-toolset">
            <div class="left">
                <button data-tool="menu" class="sk-tool icon-menu" data-title="menu"></button>
                <button data-tool="file-new" class="sk-tool icon-file-new" data-title="new"></button>
                <button data-tool="file-save" class="sk-tool icon-save" data-title="save"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="center">
                <button data-tool="select" class="sk-tool icon-select" data-title="select"></button>
                <button data-tool="text" class="sk-tool icon-text" data-title="text"></button>
                <button data-tool="pencil" class="sk-tool icon-pencil" data-title="Pencil"></button>
                <button data-tool="path" class="sk-tool icon-path" data-title="Path"></button>
                <button data-tool="polyline" class="sk-tool icon-polyline" data-title="Path"></button>
                <button data-tool="arrow" class="sk-tool icon-arrow" data-title="Arrow"></button>
                <button data-tool="highlighter" data-toolFormula="type:highlighter;shortcut:paintbrush;fill:yellow;composite:multiply,destination-over;" class="sk-tool icon-highlight" data-title="Highlighter"></button>
                <button data-tool="triangle" data-toolkit="shape" class="sk-tool icon-triangle" data-title="shape"></button>
                <button data-tool="eraser" class="sk-tool icon-eraser" data-title="Eraser"></button>
                <button data-tool="attach" class="sk-tool sk-icon icon-attachment" data-title="Attachment" style="display: inline"></button>
                <button data-tool="undo" class="sk-tool icon-undo" data-title="Undo"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="right">
                <button data-tool="guide" class="sk-tool icon-compass" data-title="Guide"></button>
                <button data-tool="search" class="sk-tool icon-search" data-title="Search"></button>
                <button data-tool="help" class="sk-tool icon-help" data-title="Help"></button>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!--- ORIENTATION -->
        <div id="sk-orientation"></div>

        <!--- CONTENT -->
        <div class="sk-contents">
            <div class="sk-doc" style="z-index: 0;"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.2/jquery.min.js"></script>	
{% endblock %}
{% block addJava %}
    <script>
        var SketchappImgObject = {
            idImg: "",
            codeImg: "",
            init: function () {
                $(document).ready(function () {
                    SketchappImgObject.idImg = {{idImage }};
                    SketchappImgObject.codeImg = "{{ code }}";
                    this.updateURL();
                    setTimeout(function () {
                        sk.open.json(SketchappImgObject.codeImg);
                    }, 1000);
                });
            },
            updateURL: function () {
                window.history.pushState("", "", "/apppage/" + window.btoa(SketchappImgObject.idImg));
            }
        }
    </script>
    {% if code != '' %} <!-- Edit Image -->
        <script>            
            SketchappImgObject.init();
        </script>            
    {% endif %}
    <script>
        window.onbeforeunload = function (e) {
            e = e || window.event;
            // For IE and Firefox prior to version 4
            if (e) {
                e.returnValue = 'Are you sure?';
            }
            // For Safari
            return 'Are you sure?';
        }
    </script>
{% endblock %}
